GameStrings.UI/AIArmy_Tooltip: Orders army to attack or defend a targeted location. If you target a friendly unit the A.I. army will follow that unit and defend it.
GameStrings.UI/AIAssault_Tooltip: All out attack a location.<n/>Even if that means suiciding units.<n/><c val="ff6000">Only one "Army Strategy" can be active at once.</c>
GameStrings.UI/AIAuto_Tooltip: A.I. will attack and defend as it desires.<n/>
GameStrings.UI/AIBeaconDelete_Tooltip: Delete all beacons of this type.
GameStrings.UI/AIBeaconDelete_Tooltip_Disabled: Delete all beacons of this type.<n/><c val="ff0000">No beacons of this type have been placed.</c>
GameStrings.UI/AIBuildCancel_Tooltip: Cancel action and return to main commands.
GameStrings.UI/AIBuild_Tooltip: Select build options for the A.I.
GameStrings.UI/AIBuild_Tooltip_Disabled: Select build options for the A.I.<n/><c val="ff0000">Disabled</c>
GameStrings.UI/AIClaim_Tooltip: Sends a scout to permanently view an area and/or claim a Xel'Naga Tower.
GameStrings.UI/AIClearAll_Tooltip: Clears all beacons and returns full control to the A.I.
GameStrings.UI/AIClearAll_Tooltip_Disabled: Clears all beacons and returns full control to the A.I.<n/><c val="ff0000">No beacons placed. The A.I. is controlling its forces.</c>
GameStrings.UI/AICommButtonTooltip: Open A.I. Communication AICOMMKEY<n/>-----------------------------------------------------------<n/>Direct Shortcut Hotkeys:<n/>Army ARMYKEY       Scout SCOUTKEY<n/>Detect DETECTKEY  Expand EXPANDKEY
GameStrings.UI/AICoopAllyTooltip: Ally Status and Selection<n/>Current status of this computer ally.<n/>Clicking here will enter BeaconMode for this specific ally.
GameStrings.UI/AICoopCancelRequestTooltip: Cancel outstanding resource requests from computer allies.
GameStrings.UI/AICoopDropoffTooltip: Leave BeaconMode and Select one of your DROPOFF. Pressing again will cycle through all DROPOFF. You can also manually select any unit to leave BeaconMode.
GameStrings.UI/AICoopModeTooltip: Enter BeaconMode where you can interact with your computer allies, including placing beacons for them to obey.
GameStrings.UI/AICoopRequestMineralsTooltip: Click to request minerals, computer allies will get to these asap.
GameStrings.UI/AICoopRequestTooltip: Outstanding mineral and vespene requests, computer allies will get to these asap.
GameStrings.UI/AICoopRequestVespeneTooltip: Click to request vespene, computer allies will get to these asap.
GameStrings.UI/AICoopSelectText: Use above buttons to select A.I. to order.
GameStrings.UI/AIDefend_Tooltip: Defend a large general area.<n/><c val="ff6000">Only one "Army Strategy" can be active at once.</c>
GameStrings.UI/AIDetect_Tooltip: Orders the A.I. to provide detection at targeted location. If you target a friendly unit the A.I. detector will follow that unit.
GameStrings.UI/AIExit_Tooltip: Exit A.I. Communication.<n/><c val="ff6000">You can also right-click in the world or select any unit to exit this mode.</c>
GameStrings.UI/AIExpand_Tooltip: Orders the A.I. to expand to targeted location as soon as possible.
GameStrings.UI/AIGoto_Tooltip: View the next beacon of this type.
GameStrings.UI/AIGoto_Tooltip_Disabled: View the next beacon of this type.<n/><c val="ff0000">No beacons of this type have been placed.</c>
GameStrings.UI/AIHarass_Tooltip: Cautiously attack a location, retreating as needed.<n/>This mode may also leave to defend elsewhere.<n/><c val="ff6000">Only one "Army Strategy" can be active at once.</c>
GameStrings.UI/AIIdle_Tooltip: Orders the A.I. to hang out at this specific location, the A.I. will still help defend elsewhere as needed, but will not attack in this mode.<n/><c val="ff6000">Only one "Army Strategy" can be active at once.</c>
GameStrings.UI/AIMinerals_Tooltip_Disabled: Request Minerals from any A.I.<n/><c val="ff0000">Resource trading not available yet.</c>
GameStrings.UI/AIRally_Tooltip: Sets building rally point for new army units for the A.I.
GameStrings.UI/AIScout_Tooltip: Orders the A.I. to scout a general location or claim a nearby Xel'Naga Tower.
GameStrings.UI/AIVespene_Tooltip_Disabled: Request Vespene from any A.I.<n/><c val="ff0000">Resource trading not available yet.</c>
GameStrings.UI/AchievementDisable: Achievements have been disabled due to cheat usage. To enable achievements again, start a new game or load a saved game.

GameStrings.UI/ChatPrivacyToolTipFriendChat: <c val="ffffff">Chat Message Privacy:</c><n/>When enabled, all chat messages from players not on your friends list will be rejected.
GameStrings.UI/ChatPrivacyToolTipFriendInvite: <c val="ffffff">Invite Privacy:</c><n/>When enabled, all party, game, and chat channel invites from players not on your friends list will be rejected.
GameStrings.UI/ChatPrivacyToolTipGameStatus: <c val="ffffff">Automatic Busy Status:</c><n/>When enabled, your status will be automatically set to Busy while playing matches. While in a match, features such as toasts and in-line chat from outside the match will be suppressed.  When you return to the main menu, your status will be restored to its previous setting.
GameStrings.UI/ChatPrivacyToolTipLocalPlayerFinder: <c val="ffffff">Players Near You:</c><n/>When enabled, this feature allows you to see other players on your network who are currently online. These players will be displayed by their character ID. Disabling this feature prevents both you from seeing other players on your network and them from seeing you.<n/><n/>Note: Toggling this feature may require some time to take effect.
GameStrings.UI/ChatTimestampsTooltip: <c val="ffffff">Show Timestamps:</c><n/>When enabled, timestamps will appear in chat.<n/>Note: only new chat messages will have timestamps.
GameStrings.UI/ChatToolTipEnableAlliedChat: <c val="ffffff">Enable Allied Chat:</c><n/>When enabled you will automatically join Allied Chat at the start of the game. This option can be toggled at the beginning of the game.

GameStrings.UI/GameplayOptionsTooltips/AITeammates: <c val="ffffff">Play with AI Teammates:</c><n/>Check this if you would prefer to fill the rest of the empty party slots with AI teammates for this game.
GameStrings.UI/GameplayOptionsTooltips/AllowWindowRe: <c val="ffffff">Allow Window Restore:</c><n/>When enabled, StarCraft II can automatically restore the window from a minimized state when important events occur, such as entering a game.
GameStrings.UI/GameplayOptionsTooltips/ClickThroughM: <c val="ffffff">Enable Right-Click Through Minimap:</c><n/>When enabled, right-clicks on the Minimap will pass through to the world.
GameStrings.UI/GameplayOptionsTooltips/ControlGroupM: <c val="ffffff">Control Groups:</c><n/>Determines the behavior of Control Group Buttons.<n/><n/><c val="ffffff">Normal:</c> Buttons are visible and can be clicked by the mouse.<n/><c val="ffffff">Hidden:</c> Buttons are not visible.<n/><c val="ffffff">Unclickable:</c> Buttons are visible but can not be clicked by the mouse.<n/><c val="ffffff">Unassignable:</c> Buttons are visible. Control groups may be recalled but not assigned with mouse clicks.
GameStrings.UI/GameplayOptionsTooltips/ExpansionLeve: <c val="ffffff">Expansion Level:</c><n/>Selects the expansion level that Matchmaking and Custom Games are played on.
GameStrings.UI/GameplayOptionsTooltips/FlyerHelper: <c val="ffffff">Show Flyer Helper:</c><n/>Flyer helpers are indicators that display the position of flying units on the terrain. This setting determines when they will be displayed.<n/><n/><c val="ffffff">None:</c> Never show flyer helpers<n/><c val="ffffff">Selected:</c> Selected and pre-target units only<n/><c val="ffffff">Always:</c> Show all flyer helpers
GameStrings.UI/GameplayOptionsTooltips/GameSpeed: <c val="ffffff">Game Speed:</c><n/>Determines how fast the game is played. All ladder matches are played on the "Faster" speed. You can lower the game speed to practice.
GameStrings.UI/GameplayOptionsTooltips/GridHint: <c val="ffffff">Display Build Grid:</c><n/>Displays a grid around a building during placement.  Use this to see how much space lies between buildings.
GameStrings.UI/GameplayOptionsTooltips/SelectAllConj: <c val="ffffff">Select All Larvae:</c><n/>When enabled, selecting a single Larva will select all attached to the same Hatchery.
GameStrings.UI/GameplayOptionsTooltips/SelectUncontr: <c val="ffffff">Enable Enemy Unit Selection:</c><n/>When enabled, you can select units that you can't control including neutral and enemy units.
GameStrings.UI/GameplayOptionsTooltips/ShowAlerts: <c val="ffffff">Show Alerts:</c><n/>When enabled, in-game alerts will be displayed on the left hand side of the screen.
GameStrings.UI/GameplayOptionsTooltips/ShowCurrentOr: <c val="ffffff">Show Current Order Indicator:</c><n/>Displays an indicator on the terrain when units are issued a movement or attack command.
GameStrings.UI/GameplayOptionsTooltips/ShowUnitPoint: <c val="ffffff">Display Experience Points:</c><n/>When enabled, floating text will be displayed over units and structures that give credit towards your score when created or killed.
GameStrings.UI/GameplayOptionsTooltips/ShowWorkerSta: <c val="ffffff">Always Show Worker Status:</c><n/>When enabled, the current and ideal number of workers will always be displayed above harvestable vespene geysers and town halls.
GameStrings.UI/GameplayOptionsTooltips/SimpleCommand: <c val="ffffff">Enable Simple Command Card:</c><n/>Enables a more simplified view of the command card.
GameStrings.UI/GameplayOptionsTooltips/SpeechLocale: <c val="ffffff">Speech and Movie Language:</c><n/>Specifies the language of speech and movies in the game.<n/><n/><c val="FF2222">Changing this option requires a game restart to take effect.</c>
GameStrings.UI/GameplayOptionsTooltips/Teen: <c val="ffffff">Reduced Violence:</c><n/>When enabled, limits the amount of blood displayed in the game and during cut scenes. Also turns off damage-specific death animations on Terran units.
GameStrings.UI/GameplayOptionsTooltips/TextLocale: <c val="ffffff">Text Language:</c><n/>Specifies the language of text in the game.<n/><n/><c val="FF2222">Changing this option requires a game restart to take effect.</c>
GameStrings.UI/GameplayOptionsTooltips/UnitStatus: <c val="ffffff">Show Unit Life Bars:</c><n/>Determines how unit life bars are displayed.<n/><n/><c val="ffffff">Normal:</c> Only show when holding<k val="StatusAll"/><n/><c val="ffffff">Targeting:</c> Shows friendly units when targeting a beneficial ability and enemy units when targeting a harmful ability<n/><c val="ffffff">Selected:</c> Selected units only<n/><c val="ffffff">Damaged:</c> Only show for units with less than their maximum life, energy, or shields<n/><c val="ffffff">Always:</c> Show all unit life bars
GameStrings.UI/GameplayOptions_RestartDialog: Some of your gameplay options require a game restart to take effect.  Would you like to restart now?
GameStrings.UI/GameplayOptions_RestartWarnDialog: Your gameplay options have been saved, but some changes will not go into effect until you restart StarCraft II.
GameStrings.UI/GlueButton/Tooltip/InStarterEdition: Unavailable to free users.  Make any purchase to unlock this permission.
GameStrings.UI/GovernmentSplashDialogKR: 본 게임물은 두 가지 등급(‘12세이용가’ 및 ‘청소년이용불가’)으로 분류되었습니다. 이용자의 연령은 게임 접속 시 자동으로 확인됩니다. <c val="f7bc07">만12세 이상 만18세 미만</c>의 어린이나 청소년은 ‘12세이용가’ 콘텐츠만 이용할 수 있으며, 만12세 미만의 어린이나 청소년이 이용하기에 부적절합니다.
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsChangedInfo: Your graphic settings are different than what this game was saved with. Would you like to change your graphic setting to be the same as the saved game?<n/><n/>If you select no, it's possible that the play experience may be affected.
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsOptions/QualityExceedsMaximum: Your graphics settings exceed the maximum recommended selection for your system which may result in poor performance and instability. Are you sure?
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsOptionsDialogs/Teen: Unchecking the <c val="ffff00">Reduced Violence</c> option will change your client from a 12+ rated game to an 18+ rated game. Are you sure you want to continue?
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsOptionsTooltips/Antialias: <c val="ffffff">Antialias:</c><n/>Will reduce aliasing and smoothen edges in the game but may reduce frame rate.<n/><n/>Antialiasing relies on your graphics card and requires Medium Shaders or better.
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsOptionsTooltips/Api: <c val="ffffff">Render API:</c><n/>This will allow you to change which renderer that the game will use. Different options will change rendering performance and memory usage.<n/><n/>It is advisable to change this option only if you have issues.<n/><n/><c val="FF2222">Changing this option requires a game restart to take effect.</c>
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsOptionsTooltips/BitDepth: <c val="ffffff">Bit Depth:</c><n/>Refers to the range of colors drawn to the screen.  32-bit allows a far greater range of colors than 16-bit.
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsOptionsTooltips/DisplayMode: <c val="ffffff">Display Mode:</c><n/>Allows you to change the primary display mode of the game to Fullscreen, Windowed, or Windowed (Fullscreen).  Windowed modes may cause a drop in performance.
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsOptionsTooltips/DriverOutOfDa: <c val="ffffff">Out of Date:</c><n/>Your display driver is out of date.  This may cause a drop in performance.
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsOptionsTooltips/EffectsQualit: <c val="ffffff">Effects Quality:</c><n/>Determines the detail level on all particle, ribbon, and splat effects.  These include explosions, dust, tread, and beams.<n/><n/>Effects Quality relies on your computer's processor (CPU).<n/><n/><c val="ffffff">Low:</c> 75% reduction<n/><c val="ffffff">Medium:</c> 50% reduction<n/><c val="ffffff">High:</c> 25% reduction<n/><c val="ffffff">Ultra:</c> No reduction<n/><n/><c val="ffffff">Suggested: %val%</c>
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsOptionsTooltips/Gamma: <c val="ffffff">Gamma:</c><n/>Determines the overall brightness of the game.  Use this if your monitor causes the game to be too bright or too dark.
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsOptionsTooltips/GlueThemeLabe: <c val="ffffff">Background Model:</c><n/>Changes the background of the out-of-game menu screens.<n/><n/><c val="FF2222">This option is not available while a promotional homescreen is active.</c>
<c val="ffffff">Background Model:</c><n/>Changes the background of the out-of-game menu screens.
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsOptionsTooltips/GraphicsQuali: <c val="ffffff">Graphics Quality:</c><n/>Determines the overall graphics quality.  This sets all advanced options below.  The default value is the suggested level for your machine.<n/><n/><c val="ffffff">Suggested: %val%</c>
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsOptionsTooltips/IndirectShado: <c val="ffffff">Indirect Shadows:</c><n/>Enables casting of indirect ambient shadows (also called screen space ambient occlusion).<n/><n/>Affects only story mode sets and cut scenes.<n/><n/>Requires Ultra shaders. Indirect ambient shadows heavily relies on your graphics card.<n/><n/><c val="ffffff">Suggested: %val%</c>
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsOptionsTooltips/LightingQuali: <c val="ffffff">Lighting Quality:</c><n/>Allows greater realism on all lighting effects.<n/><n/>Lighting Quality relies on your graphics card. Select High Shaders to unlock Lighting Quality at Medium or better.<n/><n/>Each setting from Low to Ultra increases the number of lights. In addition:<n/><c val="ffffff">High:</c> Local lights will cast shadows<n/><c val="ffffff">Ultra:</c> Ambient occlusion on local lights<n/><n/><c val="ffffff">Suggested: %val%</c>
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsOptionsTooltips/MaximumTextur: </n></n><c val="ff0000">Setting your texture quality above %textureQuality% may result in poor performance and long load times.</c>
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsOptionsTooltips/Model: <c val="ffffff">Model Quality:</c><n/>High quality models allow for more variety in various models.  You'll notice this most in death and build animations and the backgrounds for space platform maps.<n/><n/>Select Medium Shaders or higher to unlock High Model Quality.<n/><n/><c val="ffffff">Low:</c> Death, build, and other effects share a simple model<n/><c val="ffffff">High:</c> All models are unique and higher quality<n/><n/><c val="ffffff">Suggested: %val%</c><n/><n/><c val="FF2222">Changing this option requires a game restart to take effect.</c>
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsOptionsTooltips/Movies: <c val="ffffff">Movie Quality:</c><n/>Determines the quality of cinematic cutscenes and movies played within campaign levels and mission briefings.<n/><n/>Movie Quality relies on your computer's processor (CPU).<n/><n/><c val="ffffff">Low:</c> Standard Definition<n/><c val="ffffff">High:</c> High Definition<n/><n/><c val="ffffff">Suggested: %val%</c>
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsOptionsTooltips/PhysicsQualit: <c val="ffffff">Physics Quality:</c><n/>Determines the realism of colliding objects and gravity.<n/><n/>Physics Quality relies on your computer's processor (CPU).<n/><n/>Each setting from Medium to Extreme increases the number of possible active physics objects. In addition:<n/><c val="ffffff">Off:</c> No physics simulation<n/><c val="ffffff">High:</c> Ragdolls enabled<n/><n/><c val="ffffff">Suggested: %val%</c>
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsOptionsTooltips/Portraits: <c val="ffffff">Unit Portraits:</c><n/>Allows you to change the way that unit portraits are displayed.<n/><n/>Fully three-dimensional unit portraits have a higher performance cost.<n/><n/><c val="ffffff">Suggested: %val%</c>
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsOptionsTooltips/PostProcessin: <c val="ffffff">Post-Processing Quality:</c><n/>Determines the quality of selection halos and depth-of-field.<n/><n/>Post-Processing relies on your graphics card.<n/><n/><c val="ffffff">Low:</c> Displacement enabled<n/><c val="ffffff">Medium:</c> Halos enabled<n/><c val="ffffff">Ultra:</c> Depth-of-Field enabled<n/><n/><c val="ffffff">Suggested: %val%</c>
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsOptionsTooltips/ReflectionQua: <c val="ffffff">Reflections:</c><n/>Enables reflections on creep and water.<n/><n/>Reflections rely on your computer's processor (CPU).<n/><n/><c val="ffffff">Suggested: %val%</c>
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsOptionsTooltips/RefreshRate: <c val="ffffff">Refresh Rate:</c><n/>Refers to the number of times the image is drawn to the monitor.  Some players may see a flicker if the refresh rate is too low.<n/><n/><c val="ffffff">Suggested: Default</c>
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsOptionsTooltips/Resolution: <c val="ffffff">Resolution:</c><n/>Higher resolutions will result in increased clarity, but this greatly affects performance.  Choose a resolution that matches the aspect ratio of your monitor.<n/><n/><c val="ffffff">Suggested: %val%</c>
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsOptionsTooltips/ShaderDetail: <c val="ffffff">Shader Quality:</c><n/>This determines how complex your shaders are, which impacts a variety of special effects.  This can have a great impact on visual quality and performance.<n/><n/>Shader Quality relies on your graphics card.<n/><n/><c val="ffffff">Low:</c> Simplified shaders, light maps and directional lights only<n/><c val="ffffff">Medium:</c> Simplified HDR, normal maps, specular highlights and improved fog of war<n/><c val="ffffff">High:</c> Soft shadows, detail lights, ambient occlusion, improved cloaking and soft particles<n/><c val="ffffff">Ultra:</c> True HDR, translucent shadows, parallax mapping and volumetric materials<c val="ffffff"><n/><n/><c val="ffffff">Suggested: %val%</c>%supported%
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsOptionsTooltips/ShadowQuality: <c val="ffffff">Shadow Quality:</c><n/>Allows greater detail on all shadows cast.<n/><n/>Shadow Quality relies on your graphics card. Low Shadows is only available for Low Shaders.  Select Medium Shaders to unlock Shadow Quality at Medium or better.<n/><n/><c val="ffffff">Low:</c> Blob shadows only<n/><c val="ffffff">Medium:</c> Real-time shadows<n/><c val="ffffff">High:</c> Improved shadow resolution and water shadows<n/><c val="ffffff">Ultra:</c> Best shadow resolution and transparent shadows<n/><n/><c val="ffffff">Suggested: %val%</c>
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsOptionsTooltips/Teen: <c val="ffffff">Reduced Violence:</c><n/>When enabled, limits the amount of blood displayed in the game and during cut scenes. Also turns off damage-specific death animations on Terran units.
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsOptionsTooltips/TerrainQualit: <c val="ffffff">Terrain Quality:</c><n/>Allows greater detail on the terrain.  Raising Terrain Quality will increase the foliage, fog, water, and creep detail.<n/><n/>Terrain Quality relies on your graphics card.<n/><n/><c val="ffffff">Low:</c> No foliage and simple water and creep<n/><c val="ffffff">Medium:</c> Simple water, improved creep, little foliage<n/><c val="ffffff">High:</c> Realistic water and more foliage<n/><c val="ffffff">Ultra:</c> Water caustics and all foliage<n/><n/><c val="ffffff">Suggested: %val%</c>
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsOptionsTooltips/TextureQualit: <c val="ffffff">Texture Quality:</c><n/>Determines the clarity and size of textures used throughout the game.  Higher texture quality will result in more detail, but it requires more video memory.<n/><n/>Texture Quality relies on your total video memory (VRAM).<n/><n/><c val="ffffff">Low:</c> 128 MB<n/><c val="ffffff">Medium:</c> 256 MB<n/><c val="ffffff">High:</c> 512 MB<n/><c val="ffffff">Ultra:</c> 1024 MB<n/><n/><c val="ffffff">Suggested: %val%</c>
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsOptionsTooltips/VerticalSync: <c val="ffffff">Vertical Sync:</c><n/>Synchronizes your frame rate to some fraction of your monitor's refresh rate.
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsOptions_CannotSupportHighShad: <n/><n/><c val="FF2222">Your hardware cannot support High Shaders or higher.</c>
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsOptions_CannotSupportMediumSh: <n/><n/><c val="FF2222">Your hardware cannot support Medium Shaders or higher.</c>
GameStrings.UI/GraphicsOptions_CannotSupportUltraSha: <n/><n/><c val="FF2222">Your hardware cannot support Ultra Shaders or higher.</c>

GameStrings.UI/HandicapTip50: Units owned by this player have 50% of their normal life & shields.

GameStrings.UI/HandicapTip70: Units owned by this player have 70% of their normal life & shields.

GameStrings.UI/HelpControl_Abilities_Description: Use an active ability. Note: some heroes have more active abilities than others.
GameStrings.UI/HelpControl_Abilities_Name: Use Active Abilities (Q, W, E, R, D, 1, 2, 3, 4)
GameStrings.UI/HelpControl_AllChat_Description: Initiates a chat that can be viewed by all players. Note: this command only works in Custom Games.
GameStrings.UI/HelpControl_AlliedChat_Description: Initiates a chat that can only be viewed by allies.
GameStrings.UI/HelpControl_Animations_Description: Perform a special animation for all players to see.
GameStrings.UI/HelpControl_Animations_Name: Special Animations (Enter, type "/dance" or "/cheer", then Enter)
GameStrings.UI/HelpControl_AttackMove_Description: Move to the target location and engage nearby enemies along the way.
GameStrings.UI/HelpControl_Attack_Description: Move to the enemy target and attack it until it is destroyed.
GameStrings.UI/HelpControl_Attack_Name: Attack (Right-click on enemy) or (A, then Left-click on enemy)
GameStrings.UI/HelpControl_BlockCommunication_Descri: Prevents a player from communicating with you through chat messages and pings. To block a player while you are in-game, press enter, type /block into chat, press tab to cycle through players, and then press enter again. You can unblock players from the Social tab of the Options menu.
GameStrings.UI/HelpControl_CenterCamera_Description: Moves the camera so your hero is in the center.
GameStrings.UI/HelpControl_CycleRecipients_Descripti: After initiating chat, press Tab to cycle through recipients.
GameStrings.UI/HelpControl_InitiateChat_Description: Opens the chat bar. After typing a message, press Enter to send it. To cancel a message, press Escape.
GameStrings.UI/HelpControl_Mount_Description: Get on your mount to travel faster. To dismount, attack an enemy or press Z while mounted. If you are struck while mounted, you will automatically be dismounted.
GameStrings.UI/HelpControl_MoveCamera_Description: Scrolls the map by moving the mouse to the edges of the screen, holding down the Middle Mouse button and moving the mouse, or by pressing the Arrow Keys.
GameStrings.UI/HelpControl_MoveCamera_Name: Move Camera (Move Mouse to Edge of Screen), (Middle Mouse Button), or (Arrow Keys)
GameStrings.UI/HelpControl_Move_Description: Move to the target location without engaging enemies along the way.
GameStrings.UI/HelpControl_PartyChat_Description: Initiates a chat that can be viewed only by members of your party.
GameStrings.UI/HelpControl_Ping_Description: Displays a visual indicator on the minimap and plays an audio tone to allies.
GameStrings.UI/HelpControl_Ping_Name: Ping (Alt + G, then Left-click ground or minimap)
GameStrings.UI/HelpControl_QueuingCommands_Descripti: Issue a series of commands to perform in succession.<n/>Example: Hold Shift, press Z to begin mounting, Right-click on the ground, then release Shift. Your Hero will move to the specified location immediately after he gets on his mount.
GameStrings.UI/HelpControl_Reply_Description: Initiates a reply to the last Blizzard message received.
GameStrings.UI/HelpControl_Stop_Description: Orders your hero to stop moving.
GameStrings.UI/HelpControl_Talents_Description: View statistics about your hero and talents.
GameStrings.UI/HelpGameMechanic_BruiserMinions_Descr:
• [ph]Super strong minions
  • [ph]Spawns in the lane where the fortification closest to the Palace is destroyed.
GameStrings.UI/HelpGameMechanic_Bushes_Description:
• These sight blockers hide whatever is in and behind them from heroes on the ground.
  • Heroes on the ground must stand inside or walk through sight blockers to see what is on the other side.
  • Flying heroes are not affected and can act as spotters to see into or through sight blockers.
GameStrings.UI/HelpGameMechanic_Experience_Descripti:
• Experience is earned when a teammate is close to an enemy minion when it dies, when an enemy hero dies, or when an enemy fortification is destroyed.
  • Experience earned is shared across the team.
  • Leveling up gives you talents and better hero stats.
GameStrings.UI/HelpGameMechanic_FogofWar_Description: • Fog of War limits a team's vision to what its members and minions can see.
GameStrings.UI/HelpGameMechanic_Gates_Description:
• Allies can pass through but enemies cannot.
  • Attack gates to destroy them.
GameStrings.UI/HelpGameMechanic_HealthGlobes_Descrip:
• These globes drop off some enemy minions when they are killed.
  • Walk over them to gain health and mana.
  • Each hero gains the full amount of the health globe when it is collected.
GameStrings.UI/HelpGameMechanic_MercenaryCamps_Descr: • [ph]Defeat these camps and they will fight for you or drop map mechanic stuff
GameStrings.UI/HelpGameMechanic_Moonwells_Descriptio:
• Right-click a friendly moonwell to regain health and mana.
  • [ph]Wait to use it again.
GameStrings.UI/HelpGameMechanic_TowerAmmunition_Desc:
• Towers always target minions first and then heroes.
  • Some towers have limited ammunition and will stop firing when the ammunition is used up.
  • Ammunition replenishes itself over time.
GameStrings.UI/HelpGameMechanic_VisionTowers_Descrip:
• These towers provide a large sight radius when secured by a hero
  • If an enemy hero approaches, the tower becomes contested and will not provide vision until it is under a single team's control again.
GameStrings.UI/HelpReturnPanel_Text: <s val="HelpReturnPanelHeader">New Settings</s><n/>Below are new settings which can be configured in the Options menu.<n/>Simple Command Card: Alters command card to emphasize key commands<n/>Enable Enemy Unit Selection: Allows you to select enemy and neutral targets<n/>Display Experience Points: Shows experience points gained over units<n/>Starting Worker Rally: Starting workers automatically gather minerals<n/><n/><s val="HelpReturnPanelHeader">Other Changes</s><n/>Below is a list of buttons that have been added or moved in-game.<n/><n/>A Select All Army button has been added above the minimap<n/>The Menu and Help buttons are now above the command card<n/>The Achievements and Message Log buttons are now in Menu
GameStrings.UI/HelpReturnPanel_Text_1: Command card now emphasizes key commands
GameStrings.UI/HelpReturnPanel_Text_3: Experience points gained are displayed over units
GameStrings.UI/HelpReturnPanel_Text_6: Select your army using the Army button above the minimap
GameStrings.UI/HelpReturnPanel_Text_7: Menu and Help are now above the command card
GameStrings.UI/HelpReturnPanel_Text_8: Achievements and Message Log are now in Menu
GameStrings.UI/HelpReturnPanel_Text_9: You can change your settings by pressing Go To Options.
GameStrings.UI/HelpWelcomePanel_LearningToPlayText: Learn more about the game's core concepts
GameStrings.UI/HelpWelcomePanel_NeedHelpText: Visit Blizzard's Heroes of the Storm support site for help
GameStrings.UI/HeroSelectPanel/FilterAssassinButton/: Assassins use high burst damage to kill enemy heroes
GameStrings.UI/HeroSelectPanel/FilterSiegeButton/Too: Specialists are unique in their contributions
GameStrings.UI/HeroSelectPanel/FilterSupportButton/T: Support heroes help teammates perform to their fullest potential
GameStrings.UI/HeroSelectPanel/FilterTankButton/Tool: Warriors have high health and help control the flow of battle
GameStrings.UI/HijackRecoverMessage: The game has been recovered from a replay.
GameStrings.UI/Hotkey/Tooltip/CameraCenter: Centers the camera on the selected unit.
GameStrings.UI/Hotkey/Tooltip/CameraFollow: Locks the camera onto the selected unit.

GameStrings.UI/Hotkey/Tooltip/CameraSave1: Saves the current camera location as Camera Location 2.
GameStrings.UI/Hotkey/Tooltip/CameraSave2: Saves the current camera location as Camera Location 3.

GameStrings.UI/Hotkey/Tooltip/CameraSave6: Saves the current camera location as Camera Location 7.
GameStrings.UI/Hotkey/Tooltip/CameraSave7: Saves the current camera location as Camera Location 8.

GameStrings.UI/Hotkey/Tooltip/CameraView1: Moves the camera to Camera Location 2.

GameStrings.UI/Hotkey/Tooltip/DisplayMode: Toggle Display Mode between Windowed and Windowed Fullscreen.

GameStrings.UI/Hotkey/Tooltip/LeaderAPM: Toggles the APM (Actions Per Minute) leaderboard.

GameStrings.UI/HotkeyOptionsTooltips/HotkeyProfile: <c val="ffffff">Profile:</c><n/>Selects a set of hotkeys to use in games.
GameStrings.UI/HotkeyProfileDescription/0_Default: Standard keeps most commands on the left side of the keyboard. The first letter of the command name is often used as the hotkey.
GameStrings.UI/HotkeyProfileDescription/1_NameRightS: Designed for left-handed players. Keeps most commands on the right side of the keyboard. A few key differences to make note of:<n/>   - The F12 key is an alternate key for Escape.<n/>   - Chat moved to the Tab key.<n/>   - Control Group functionality shifted from the 1 to 0 keys to the 3 to = keys.
GameStrings.UI/HotkeyProfileDescription/2_GridLeftSi: Grid hotkeys are based on the button's position in the command card.
GameStrings.UI/HotkeyProfileDescription/3_GridRightS: Grid hotkeys are based on the button's position in the command card. A few key differences to make note of:<n/>   - The F12 key is an alternate key for Escape.<n/>   - Chat moved to the Tab key.<n/>   - Control Group functionality shifted from the 1 to 0 keys to the 3 to = keys.
GameStrings.UI/HotkeyProfileDescription/4_Classic: Classic uses the hotkeys from the original StarCraft (where possible).
GameStrings.UI/HotkeyPublishMessage: <n/>Your active hotkey profile is stored on Blizzard services, and is available from any machine you log into.
GameStrings.UI/HotkeySelectCommandHint: Click on a command to edit its hotkeys.
GameStrings.UI/HotkeySelectUnitHint: Click on a unit to view its commands.

GameStrings.UI/ImageUploadHelp:
Image Requirements:
  • Supported image types: DDS, PNG, JPG, and TGA

GameStrings.UI/InGameChannelTooltip: <c val="ffffff">Show Blizzard channels in-game:</c><n/>When enabled, you will remain in official Blizzard chat channels when joining a game, and those messages will display in-line while in a game.
GameStrings.UI/InGameCustomChannelTooltip: <c val="ffffff">Chat channels in-game:</c><n/>When enabled, you will remain in non-Blizzard chat channels (such as clan and group chat) when joining a game, and those messages will display in-line while in a game.
GameStrings.UI/InputOptionsTooltips: In order to use this option accessibility needs to be in enabled. Please check the option "Enable access for assistive devices" in the Universal Access System Preferences panel.  Would you like to open the System Preferences now?
GameStrings.UI/InputOptionsTooltips/AltTabDisable: <c val="ffffff">Disable Alt-Tab Shortcut:</c><n/>Disables the Alt-Tab key combination. Use this if you don't want to accidentally minimize the game.
GameStrings.UI/InputOptionsTooltips/CameraFollow: <c val="ffffff">Enable Camera Follow:</c><n/>When enabled, the camera will follow your hero as it moves around the map.
GameStrings.UI/InputOptionsTooltips/CmdTabDisable: <c val="ffffff">Disable Cmd-Tab Shortcut:</c><n/>Disables the Cmd-Tab key combination. Use this if you don't want to accidentally minimize the game.
GameStrings.UI/InputOptionsTooltips/ControlGroupMode: <c val="ffffff">Control Groups:</c><n/>Determines the behavior of Control Group Buttons.<n/><n/><c val="ffffff">Normal:</c> Buttons are visible and can be clicked by the mouse.<n/><c val="ffffff">Hidden:</c> Buttons are not visible.<n/><c val="ffffff">Unclickable:</c> Buttons are visible but can not be clicked by the mouse.
GameStrings.UI/InputOptionsTooltips/CursorConfine: <c val="ffffff">Confine Mouse Cursor:</c><n/>Determines when the mouse cursor can leave the application window in either Windowed (Fullscreen) or Windowed Display Modes.  In the Fullscreen Display Mode this setting has no effect, the cursor is always confined.<n/><n/><c val="ffffff">Smart:</c> In Windowed Fullscreen, mouse cursor is confined during games, but unconfined in menu screens.  In windowed mode, this has no effect.<n/><c val="ffffff">On:</c> Mouse cursor is always confined.<n/><c val="ffffff">Off:</c> Mouse cursor is never confined.
GameStrings.UI/InputOptionsTooltips/CursorSize: <c val="ffffff">Cursor Size:</c><n/>Determines how large your mouse cursor appears.<n/><n/>Not supported on Windows XP.
GameStrings.UI/InputOptionsTooltips/DragScrollInvert: <c val="ffffff">Invert Drag Scroll:</c><n/>Flips the direction the map scrolls while dragging the middle mouse button. This may feel more natural to some players.
GameStrings.UI/InputOptionsTooltips/DragScrollSpeed: <c val="ffffff">Drag Scroll Speed:</c><n/>Determines how fast to scroll the map while dragging the middle mouse button.
GameStrings.UI/InputOptionsTooltips/EnableFunctionKe: <c val="ffffff">Use standard function key behavior</c><n/>When selected, the top row of the keyboard behaves as function keys. Press the Fn key to use the features printed on each key. When deselected, the top row will behave according to OS settings.
GameStrings.UI/InputOptionsTooltips/KeyboardScrollSp: <c val="ffffff">Keyboard Scroll Speed:</c><n/>Determines how fast to scroll the map when using the keyboard's arrow keys.
GameStrings.UI/InputOptionsTooltips/MouseOverrideSen: <c val="ffffff">Enable Mouse Sensitivity:</c><n/>Enables setting a custom mouse sensitivity to override the setting from the operating system.
GameStrings.UI/InputOptionsTooltips/MouseScrollEnabl: <c val="ffffff">Enable Mouse Scroll:</c><n/>Enables the ability to scroll the map by placing the cursor at the edge of the screen.
GameStrings.UI/InputOptionsTooltips/MouseScrollSpeed: <c val="ffffff">Mouse Scroll Speed:</c><n/>Determines how fast to scroll the map when the cursor is at the edge of the screen.
GameStrings.UI/InputOptionsTooltips/MouseSensitivity: <c val="ffffff">Mouse Sensitivity:</c><n/>Determines how sensitive your mouse is. Higher sensitivity will cause the mouse to move faster.
GameStrings.UI/InputOptionsTooltips/MouseWheelZoom: <c val="ffffff">Enable Mouse Wheel Zoom:</c><n/>Allows the camera to zoom into or out of the map while using the mouse wheel.
GameStrings.UI/InputOptionsTooltips/QuickCastMode: <c val="ffffff">Quick Cast:</c><n/>Determines how attack and ability targeting behaves.<n/><n/><c val="ffffff">Off:</c> Pressing a hotkey to issue an order enters target mode and then <k pre="(" val="TargetChoose" post=")"/> issues the order.<n/><c val="ffffff">On:</c> Pressing a hotkey instantly issues the order in the direction or location of your mouse cursor.<n/><c val="ffffff">On Release:</c> Pressing a hotkey enters targeting mode and releasing the hotkey issues the order in the direction of your mouse cursor.
GameStrings.UI/InputOptionsTooltips/ReduceMouseLag: <c val="ffffff">Reduce Mouse Lag:</c><n/>Will make the mouse more responsive, but may drastically reduce frame rate.
GameStrings.UI/InputOptionsTooltips/SelectAllConjoin: <c val="ffffff">Select All Larvae:</c><n/>When enabled, selecting a single larva will select all larvae for that Hatchery.
GameStrings.UI/InputOptionsTooltips/SelectUncontroll: <c val="ffffff">Enable Enemy Unit Selection:</c><n/>When enabled, you can select units that are not under your control including enemy and neutral units.
GameStrings.UI/InputOptionsTooltips/ShowCurrentOrder: <c val="ffffff">Show Current Order Indicator:</c><n/>When enabled, issuing an order to your units will cause an indicator to be displayed on the terrain.
GameStrings.UI/InputOptionsTooltips/ShowUnitPoints: <c val="ffffff">Display Experience Points:</c><n/>When enabled, experience points will be displayed over units and structures when created or destroyed.
GameStrings.UI/InputOptionsTooltips/SmartPan: <c val="ffffff">Enable Smart Camera Pan:</c><n/>When enabled, the camera will quickly scroll (instead of jump) to a nearby unit when you click the unit's portrait.  If the unit is not currently in view, it will jump to the location instead.<n/><n/>Double-tapping a control group hotkey will always cause the camera to jump.
GameStrings.UI/InputOptionsTooltips/SwapCtrlCmd: <c val="ffffff"> Use Command instead of Control for hotkeys:</c><n/>Use this if you want to use the Command key modifier for the hotkey commands instead of the Control key.
GameStrings.UI/InputOptionsTooltips/SystemUtilityKey: <c val="ffffff">Disable OS Keyboard Shortcuts:</c><n/>Disables the operating system keyboard shortcuts. Use this if you don't want to accidentally fire operating system shortcuts during the game.
GameStrings.UI/InputOptionsTooltips/WinKeyDisable: <c val="ffffff">Disable Windows Key:</c><n/>Disables the Windows key. Use this if you don't want to accidentally minimize the game.

GameStrings.UI/RankedPlay/CasualLeagueTooltip:
Hero LeagueIn this league players can queue by themselves or in parties of up to four players to be matched against players of similar skill.League Rank
  • Your rank is a representation of your skill where each Rank is about 2% of the players in the league.
  • To rise in ranks, win matches and earn points.
  • No points are lost when losing matches between ranks 50 to 40.
  • Placement Rank: Your rank is not determined until you have completed a number of games to determine your skill level.
GameStrings.UI/RankedPlay/TeamLeagueTooltip:
Team LeagueIn this league full parties are matched against other full parties of similar skill.League Rank
  • Your rank is a representation of your skill where each Rank is about 2% of the players in the league.

  • Placement Rank: Your rank is not determined until you have completed a number of games to determine your skill level.

GameStrings.UI/SoundOptionsTooltips/AlertFadeVolume: <c val="ffffff">Game Volume During Alerts:</c><n/>This determines the volume level of other game sounds while alerts are playing. Lower this if you are having trouble hearing alerts over other game sounds.
GameStrings.UI/SoundOptionsTooltips/AltSoundtrack: <c val="ffffff">Soundtrack:</c><n/>Choose the music in Multiplayer games.
GameStrings.UI/SoundOptionsTooltips/Ambience: <c val="ffffff">Enable Ambient Sounds:</c><n/>Enables ambient sound effects based on the environment, such as wind or water sounds.
GameStrings.UI/SoundOptionsTooltips/AmbienceVolume: <c val="ffffff">Ambience Volume:</c><n/>Determines the volume of ambient sound effects.
GameStrings.UI/SoundOptionsTooltips/Channels: <c val="ffffff">Sound Channels:</c><n/>Determines the number of sound effects that can play simultaneously. Lower this number to improve performance.
GameStrings.UI/SoundOptionsTooltips/Effects: <c val="ffffff">Enable Sound Effects:</c><n/>Enables standard gameplay sound effects.
GameStrings.UI/SoundOptionsTooltips/EffectsVolume: <c val="ffffff">Sound Effects Volume:</c><n/>Determines the volume of standard gameplay sound effects.
GameStrings.UI/SoundOptionsTooltips/Errors: <c val="ffffff">Enable Error Sounds:</c><n/>Enables sounds that are played in response to an invalid command.
GameStrings.UI/SoundOptionsTooltips/Global: <c val="ffffff">Play in Background:</c><n/>Allows the game to continue playing sound when it is not the focus window.
GameStrings.UI/SoundOptionsTooltips/HeadphoneMode: <c val="ffffff">Headphone Mode:</c><n/>Enables software emulation for headphone surround sound.
GameStrings.UI/SoundOptionsTooltips/Herds: <c val="ffffff">Enable Group Sounds:</c><n/>Enables additional sounds for groups of units performing the same activity.
GameStrings.UI/SoundOptionsTooltips/MasterVolume: <c val="ffffff">Master Volume:</c><n/>This controls the volume of all sounds in the game.
GameStrings.UI/SoundOptionsTooltips/Movement: <c val="ffffff">Enable Movement Sounds:</c><n/>Enables sounds related to units moving, such as footsteps or engines.
GameStrings.UI/SoundOptionsTooltips/MusicContinuous: <c val="ffffff">Enable Continuous Music:</c><n/>Enables uninterrupted background music.
GameStrings.UI/SoundOptionsTooltips/MusicVolume: <c val="ffffff">Music Volume:</c><n/>Determines the volume of background music.
GameStrings.UI/SoundOptionsTooltips/OutputDevice: <c val="ffffff">Output Device:</c><n/>The output device is where your sound will play. Default will match your system's output device. Use this if you want the game to play through headphones or a different set of speakers.
GameStrings.UI/SoundOptionsTooltips/Quality: <c val="ffffff">Sound Quality:</c><n/>Determines the audio fidelity. Higher quality settings will sound better but may slow down the game.
GameStrings.UI/SoundOptionsTooltips/Ready: <c val="ffffff">Enable Announcer:</c><n/>Allows you to hear phrases from the map announcer including: countdowns, map objective notifications, and death notifications.
GameStrings.UI/SoundOptionsTooltips/ReadyVolume: <c val="ffffff">Announcer Volume:</c><n/>Determines the volume of announcers.
GameStrings.UI/SoundOptionsTooltips/Responses: <c val="ffffff">Enable Response Sounds:</c><n/>Enables response sounds for when you order or select units.
GameStrings.UI/SoundOptionsTooltips/Reverb: <c val="ffffff">Enable Reverb:</c><n/>Reverb is a slight echo added to all sound effects. It increases sound realism, but disabling this may improve performance.
GameStrings.UI/SoundOptionsTooltips/Sound: <c val="ffffff">Enable Sound:</c><n/>Enables all sound during gameplay.
GameStrings.UI/SoundOptionsTooltips/SpeakerMode: <c val="ffffff">Speaker Setup:</c><n/>Set this to match your speaker setup. Choose Stereo for headphones or standard two-speaker setups.
GameStrings.UI/SoundOptionsTooltips/SpeakerMode_Wind: <c val="ffffff">Speaker Setup:</c><n/>Windows only permits changing the speaker setup using the Sound Control Panel. This is the setup currently selected by the Control Panel.
GameStrings.UI/SoundOptionsTooltips/UI: <c val="ffffff">Enable Interface Sounds:</c><n/>Enables sound effects on the user interface, such as buttons and menus.
GameStrings.UI/SoundOptionsTooltips/UIVolume: <c val="ffffff">Interface Sounds Volume:</c><n/>Determines the volume of user interface sounds, such as buttons and menus.
GameStrings.UI/SoundOptionsTooltips/Voices: <c val="ffffff">Enable Voices:</c><n/>Enables voiced dialogue and responses.
GameStrings.UI/SoundOptionsTooltips/VoicesVolume: <c val="ffffff">Voices Volume:</c><n/>Determines the volume of dialogue and responses.
GameStrings.UI/SoundOptions_RestartDialog: Some of your sound options require a game restart to take effect. Would you like to restart now?

GameStrings.UI/StereoscopicConvergence_Tooltip: Stereo convergence controls the depth of the point of convergence where no parallax occurs. Increase convergence to push objects further out of the screen. Too much convergence can be uncomfortable if your eyes are not adjusted to stereo.
GameStrings.UI/StereoscopicEnable_Tooltip: Enables stereoscopic support. The game must be in fullscreen mode to activate the effect.
GameStrings.UI/StereoscopicOptionsPanelDescription: These options allow you to change details having to do with stereoscopic (3D) viewing.
GameStrings.UI/StereoscopicSeparation_Tooltip: Stereo separation refers to the difference in horizontal position between the right and left images. The greater the stereo separation, the greater the stereo effect. Too much separation, can be uncomfortable if your eyes are not adjusted to stereo.

GameStrings.UI/VideoOptionsInstructions: You can toggle in-game video recording by pressing CTRL-F11 while playing a game or watching a replay. Videos are stored in your user directory's StarCraft II Videos folder in Theora OGV format. Recording high quality video may considerably slow down your game experience.
GameStrings.UI/VideoOptionsTooltips/AudioQuality: <c val="ffffff">Audio Quality:</c><n/>Increasing audio quality will provide greater audio fidelity at a cost of larger video files.
GameStrings.UI/VideoOptionsTooltips/FrameRate: <c val="ffffff">Framerate:</c><n/>Framerate refers to the number of frames recorded per second. A higher framerate will result in smoother video playback at a cost of larger video files. Recording at a higher framerate may slow down your game experience.
GameStrings.UI/VideoOptionsTooltips/RecordAudioCheck: <c val="ffffff">Enable Audio:</c><n/>Enables recording audio with your video.
GameStrings.UI/VideoOptionsTooltips/RecordTriggers: <c val="ffffff">Record From Triggers:</c><n/>Enabling this option will allow you to record video from in-game triggers. Players can create maps with "MovieStartRecording" triggers to facilitate the creation of movies. Keep this option off if you do not want videos to automatically record on certain maps.
GameStrings.UI/VideoOptionsTooltips/Resolution: <c val="ffffff">Resolution:</c><n/>Determines the size in pixels of the recorded video. Higher resolutions have much better image quality, but they are slower to record. For best results, use a resolution that matches your game's aspect ratio.
GameStrings.UI/VideoOptionsTooltips/SlowGame: <c val="ffffff">Slow Game while Recording:</c><n/>Determines whether or not game time will slow down to adjust for the performance drop while recording video. This will result in better looking videos, but it cannot be used while participating in multiplayer games. Videos recorded with this option disabled will record the drop in framerate, but your audio will be unaffected.
GameStrings.UI/VideoOptionsTooltips/VideoQuality: <c val="ffffff">Video Quality:</c><n/>Determines the amount of compression used when recording your video. Greater video quality will result in better image quality but much larger video files.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/AGC: <c val="ffffff">Microphone Automatic Gain Control:</c><n/>Toggles automatic gain control for the microphone, which will adjust the outgoing sound levels to maintain a constant volume.<n/><n/><c val="ff0000">Note: This will change the operating system settings for the microphone. It will affect other applications that use the microphone while StarCraft II is running.</c>
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/ActivatedSensiti: <c val="ffffff">Microphone Activation Sensitivity:</c><n/>Determines how loudly you must speak before voice chat is activated. Keep this lower if breathing and other incidental sounds are triggering voice chat.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/ChatVolume: <c val="ffffff">Voice Chat Output Volume:</c><n/>Determines how loudly voice chat plays back.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/FadeMusicVolume: <c val="ffffff">Fade Music Level:</c><n/>This determines the level that music should play while someone is speaking.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/FadeSoundVolume: <c val="ffffff">Fade Sound Level:</c><n/>This determines the level that game sounds should play while someone is speaking. Use this if you are having trouble hearing other people over gameplay or if your game sounds are recorded while speaking.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/InputDevice: <c val="ffffff">Input Device:</c><n/>Selects the microphone or headset used for voice chat.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/Microphone: <c val="ffffff">Enable Talking:</c><n/>Enables the ability to participate in voice chat during gameplay. You must have an input device such as a microphone, headset, or built-in microphone.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/MicrophoneBoost: <c val="ffffff">Microphone Boost:</c><n/>Increases the power of a traditional microphone. This may cause distortion with USB headsets or microphones. Not all input devices support boost.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/MicrophoneHardwa: <c val="ffffff">Mute OS Microphone:</c><n/>Toggles the OS microphone mute state.<n/><n/><c val="ff0000">Note: This will affect other applications and will remain in effect when StarCraft II is not running.</c>
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/MicrophoneTest: <c val="ffffff">Microphone Test:</c><n/>Toggle the microphone test. While enabled, all voice spoken through the microphone will play back through the selected voice output device.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/MicrophoneVolume: <c val="ffffff">Microphone Volume:</c><n/>Determines how loudly audio is recorded. Increase this if others have a hard time hearing you. Disabled if Auto setting is being used.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/Mode: <c val="ffffff">Voice Chat Mode:</c><n/>Determines how your microphone is activated. Voice Activated will automatically activate chat when you speak. Push-to-Talk requires you to hold a button while speaking.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/OutputDevice: <c val="ffffff">Output Device:</c><n/>Selects the speakers or headphones used to play back voice chat. Voice chat does not need to play through the same device as the game.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/PTTHotkey: <c val="ffffff">Push-to-Talk Key:</c><n/>Determines the key used to activate voice chat. Press the button then the key you want to use to change this value.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/PTTSound: <c val="ffffff">Push-to-Talk Sound:</c><n/>When enabled, a small chime will play when you press or release your Push-to-Talk key.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/Provider: <c val="ffffff">Provider:</c><n/>Selects the voice chat input/output provider.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/VoiceChat: <c val="ffffff">Enable Voice Chat:</c><n/>Enables the ability to listen or participate in voice chat during gameplay.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/VoiceChatParenta: <c val="ff0000">Voice Chat:</c><n/>This feature has been disabled by parental control.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/VoiceToast: <c val="ffffff">Enable Voice Toasts:</c><n/>Enables the display of indicators which show who is currently speaking in voice chat.

GameStrings.Missile/UnsupportedNegativeBlendAtAndPos: Не поддерживается: отрицательное значение BlendAt[%1] и положительное значение StopAt[%2].  Mover[%3] Phase[%4]. Невозможно указать начальную точку угасания наложения фазы относительно цели, при этом одновременно указывая конечное расстояние, на котором происходит наложение фазы относительно исходной точки. Это может привести к непостоянным или некорректным алгоритмам поведения из-за непостоянного расстояния между исходной и конечной точками.
GameStrings.Missile/UnsupportedNonGroundHeightMap: CMoverMissile[%1]; Снаряды поддерживают только карту высот относительно земли. Воздушная карта высот позволяет летающим объектам плавно преодолевать уступы. В случае со снарядами это на работает, а лишь создает затруднения для снарядов, которые находятся невысоко над землей. Поэтому такая карта высот игнорируется для снарядах. /// CMoverMissile[%1]; Missiles only support the ground height map.  The air height map enables fliers to move smoothly over cliffs -- it offers no assistance to missiles and would only causes glitches in missiles that need to be near the ground.  It is therefore ignored on missiles.

GameStrings.UI/ChatPanel/HelpMessage: <s val="BattleChatSystem">Команды чата:</n>- /войти <название канала> – зайти на указанный канал;</n>- /выйти <название канала> – покинуть указанный канал;</n>- /список – список доступных каналов;</n>- /кто – список посетителей текущего канала;</n>- /<номер канала> – заменяет текущий канал на канал с указанным номером;</n>- /шепот <имя игрока> <сообщение> – послать личное сообщение;</n>- /ответ <сообщение> – ответить на личное сообщение.</s>

GameStrings.UI/ChatPanel/NotInChatMessage: Для начала чата нужно зайти на канал чата. Наберите "/войти [название канала]" или "/список", чтобы просмотреть список каналов.
GameStrings.UI/ChatPanel/TooltipPlayerName: Наберите имя /// Begin typing a name
GameStrings.UI/ChatPanel/UnknownCommandMessage: Неизвестная команда. Наберите "/помощь", чтобы увидеть список доступных команд. /// Unknown slash command. Type /help to list slash commands.
GameStrings.UI/ChatPanel/WhoMessageUnavailableUntilL: Команда для отображения списка участников станет доступна по достижении %level%-го уровня.
GameStrings.UI/ChatPrivacyCheckBoxFriendChat: Принимать сообщения чата только от друзей /// Only allow friends to send me messages
GameStrings.UI/ChatPrivacyCheckBoxFriendInvite: Принимать приглашения только от друзей /// Only allow friends to send me invites
GameStrings.UI/ChatPrivacyCheckBoxLocalPlayerFinder: Список игроков рядом с вами /// Enable Players Near You List
GameStrings.UI/ChatPrivacyToolTipFriendChat: <c val="ffffff">Ограничение сообщений чата</c><n/>Система будет игнорировать сообщения от игроков, которые не числятся в вашем списке друзей. /// <c val="ffffff">Chat Message Privacy:</c><n/>When enabled, all chat messages from players not on your friends list will be rejected.
GameStrings.UI/ChatPrivacyToolTipFriendInvite: <c val="ffffff">Ограничение приглашений</c><n/>Система будет игнорировать приглашения в группу, игру или канал чата от игроков, которые не числятся в вашем списке друзей. /// <c val="ffffff">Invite Privacy:</c><n/>When enabled, all party, game, and chat channel invites from players not on your friends list will be rejected.
GameStrings.UI/ChatPrivacyToolTipGameStatus: <c val="ffffff">Автоматический статус «Занят»</c><n/>На время матча ваш статус Battle.net будет автоматически меняться на «Занят». При этом вы перестанете видеть всплывающие оповещения и сообщения чата от пользователей, которые не участвуют с вами в одном матче. При возвращении в основное меню ваш статус будет меняться на выбранный ранее.
GameStrings.UI/ChatPrivacyToolTipLocalPlayerFinder: <c val="ffffff">Игроки рядом с вами</c><n/>Позволяет видеть игроков вашей сети, когда они входят в сеть. Эти игроки будут отображаться по ID своих персонажей. При отключении этой функции вы не сможете видеть других игроков вашей сети, а они не смогут видеть вас.<n/><n/>Примечание: чтобы эффект вступил в силу, должно пройти некоторое время. /// <c val="ffffff">Players Near You:</c><n/>When enabled, this feature allows you to see other players on your network who are currently online. These players will be displayed by their character ID. Disabling this feature prevents both you from seeing other players on your network and them from seeing you.<n/><n/>Note: Toggling this feature may require some time to take effect.
GameStrings.UI/ChatTimestampsTooltip: <c val="ffffff">Время прихода сообщений</c><n/>Эта настройка позволяет отображать время прихода сообщений в чате.<n/>Примечание: время будет отображаться только для новых сообщений.
GameStrings.UI/ChatToolTipEnableAlliedChat: <c val="ffffff">Командный чат</c><n/>Игра автоматически подключается к командному чату в начале матча. Эту функцию можно переключить в начале матча. /// <c val="ffffff">Enable Allied Chat:</c><n/>When enabled you will automatically join Allied Chat at the start of the game. This option can be toggled at the beginning of the game.
GameStrings.UI/ClubPanel/ClubPanelEmptyChatBubbleTex: Нажмите кнопку «Найти» для обзора и поиска сообществ.
GameStrings.UI/ClubPanel/ClubPanelEmptyDesc: В сообществах и кланах вы сможете общаться в модерируемых чатах, видеть, кто из участников находится в сети, и быть в курсе последних новостей.
GameStrings.UI/CmdTabDisable: Заблокировать переключение между программами /// Disable Cmd-Tab Shortcut
GameStrings.UI/ColorBlindColorByAllianceTip: Боевые единицы окрашиваются цветом, выбранным в разделе настроек «Цвета союзов – альтернативные».<n/><k val="MinimapColors"/>
GameStrings.UI/ColorByAllianceTip: Боевые единицы окрашиваются цветом, выбранным в разделе настроек «Цвета союзов».<n/><k val="MinimapColors"/>
GameStrings.UI/ColorByPlayerTip: Боевые единицы окрашиваются в цвета игроков.<n/><k val="MinimapColors"/>
GameStrings.UI/ColorByTeamTip: Для боевых единиц используются командные цвета.<n/><k val="MinimapColors"/>
GameStrings.UI/ColorOptionsTooltips/AdditionalTeamCo: <c val="ffffff">Дополнительные текстуры цветов команд</c><n/>Если разрешить эту настройку, для указанных эффектов и боевых единиц будут использоваться дополнительные текстуры цветов. Требуется перезапуск игры.
GameStrings.UI/ColorOptionsTooltips/ColorBlindMode: <c val="ffffff">Режим для людей с нарушенным цветовосприятием</c><n/>При включении этого режима для отображения сетки размещения строений и игроков в зависимости от принадлежности к команде будут использоваться альтернативные цвета. Поверхность на мини-карте станет более темной.
GameStrings.UI/ColorOptionsTooltips/OverrideColorAll: <c val="ffffff">Цвет союзников</c><n/>Позволяет выбрать цвет, которым выделяются войска и строения союзника, когда используется отображение боевых союзов на мини-карте.
GameStrings.UI/ColorOptionsTooltips/OverrideColorBli: <c val="ffffff">Цвет союзников</c><n/>Позволяет выбрать цвет, которым выделяются войска и строения союзника, когда используется отображение боевых союзов на мини-карте.
<c val="ffffff">Цвет врагов</c><n/>Позволяет выбрать цвет, которым выделяются войска и строения врагов, когда используется отображение боевых союзов на мини-карте.
<c val="ffffff">Цвет нейтрального союза</c><n/>Позволяет выбрать цвет, которым выделяются нейтральные войска и строения, когда используется отображение боевых союзов на мини-карте.
<c val="ffffff">Ваш цвет на мини-карте</c><n/>Позволяет выбрать цвет, которым выделяются на мини-карте ваши войска и строения, когда используется отображение боевых союзов на мини-карте.
<c val="ffffff">Ваш цвет</c><n/>Позволяет выбрать цвет, которым выделяются ваши войска и строения, когда используется отображение боевых союзов на мини-карте.
GameStrings.UI/ColorOptionsTooltips/OverrideColorHos: <c val="ffffff">Цвет врагов</c><n/>Позволяет выбрать цвет, которым выделяются войска и строения врагов, когда используется отображение боевых союзов на мини-карте.
GameStrings.UI/ColorOptionsTooltips/OverrideColorNeu: <c val="ffffff">Цвет нейтрального союза</c><n/>Позволяет выбрать цвет, которым выделяются нейтральные войска и строения, когда используется отображение боевых союзов на мини-карте.
GameStrings.UI/ColorOptionsTooltips/OverrideColorSel: <c val="ffffff">Ваш цвет на мини-карте</c><n/>Позволяет выбрать цвет, которым выделяются на мини-карте ваши войска и строения, когда используется отображение боевых союзов на мини-карте.
<c val="ffffff">Ваш цвет</c><n/>Позволяет выбрать цвет, которым выделяются ваши войска и строения, когда используется отображение боевых союзов на мини-карте.
GameStrings.UI/ColorOptionsTooltips/TeamColorIntensi: <c val="ffffff">Яркость цвета команды</c><n/>Регулирует яркость цвета команды на карте.
GameStrings.UI/ColorOptionsTooltips/TeamColoredLifeS: <c val="ffffff">Шкалы здоровья цвета команды</c><n/>Если эта функция активна, шкалы здоровья боевых единиц будут отображаться в цветах контролирующих их игроков.
